We’re talking ✨details✨ today. I’m pretty minimal when it comes to jewelry - if it’s not adding something to a look, I don’t really bother, but I do like to add an earring especially when my hair is back. This @_jennybird pair is perfect, I like that they’re a little chunky and not a traditional hoop. They go with everything and I’ll probably reach for them all week. Living in Los Angeles, sunglasses are a must and can be a really nice way to finish an outfit. Same goes for a great bag. Both pieces are essential for elevating a minimalistic look. What are your day to day accessory essentials?

Brittany in @philosophyofficial for @voguemagazine Mental Health dinner

Major hair change this week - I don’t usually get too personal on here but I have been struggling with postpartum hair loss for over a year - I’ve always had thin, fine hair but this has been different. 

Excessive shedding, breakage, change in texture and strength. My hair is thiiiiin y’all. 

I’ve had extensions in for the better part of that year (done by the best) trying to mask the problem and also just feel good about myself as a new mom going through a million different bodily and life changes. My goal was always to feel my best and be as low maintenance as possible in order to be present for my son and in my life. 

But candidly the amount of mental energy my hair has taken  up during this time has been exhausting. 

I finally made the decision to go without extensions and returned to my natural color in an effort to embrace where I’m at and really commit to hair health. 

You might be seeing a lot of low buns for the foreseeable future but it feels good not to be hiding anymore. Sending love and light to anyone going through something similar.

Big thanks for @anjabee and @marcmena for their immense talent and being so gentle with me
